task.summary: Moved the parameter value type creation from _algorithm to parameter.py and did a bit of clean up in _algorithm. The parameter objects in parameter.py can now be created with or without name and with kwargs as the user likes
Documented and cleaned mpi.py and fixed a python3 bug and fixed a typo in mc.py

Changed the datatype of the parameter array to U30 instead of S30, which is a byte-string in Python 3. Hence we can skip alot of decoding from parameter names esp. in tutorial_dream_hymod.py and database.py. And in likelihoods.py we do not need the clumsy __byteArrayToString function
The parameters accept all positional and keyword arguments using the somewhat complex trick function in `Parameter._get_name_from_args`.
Fixed a sorting issue in Python <= 3.5 with the class defined parameters in the `get_parameters_from_class`
